  "prompt": "How long will a Google shortened URL be available?",
  "response": "Google's URL shortening service, known as goo.gl, was officially discontinued on March 30, 2019. After this date, new links could no longer be created, and existing links would remain functional for a time but were no longer supported or guaranteed to be active indefinitely.\n\nIf you were using Google\u2019s service before the discontinuation, previously created links may still work, but Google has not guaranteed their availability for the long term. For permanent link shortening, it's advisable to use other services such as Bitly, TinyURL, or similar services that indicate their commitment to maintaining links over time. Always check the specific service's terms and policies for the best information on link longevity.",
